The Chronicle Ricky Zililo, Senior Sports Reporter ZIFA official kit sponsor Umbro has given the national association nine options to select designs for the gear national teams will don. <img class="alignnone wp-image-436747 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/away_kit-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/away_kit.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/away_kit-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The English sportswear and football equipment supplier and Zifa signed a three-year deal that will see it providing a full consignment of training equipment, travelling gear and playing kits for all national teams, including women and various age-groups. <img class="alignnone wp-image-436744 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/home_kit-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/home_kit.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/home_kit-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Umbro will supply new kit for each of the national teams’ games as well as provide replicas for sale. <img class="alignnone wp-image-436750 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/gk_kit-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/gk_kit.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/gk_kit-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Chronicle Sport has it in good authority that Zifa was given nine designs, three for the home kit, three for the away kit and another three for the alternative kit. More to follow… 